description.narrative: Statistics Sierra Leone (Stats-SL) earns a seat at the UN Statistical Commission as a result of its commitment to child poverty and enhanced capacity to generate data to be used for planning, monitoring and evaluation. The 2018 Multidimensional Child Poverty Report was launched by the Minister of Planning and Economic Development, showing that poverty declined by 11 percentile points from 77 per cent in 2010. Vulnerability and equity profiles, used to influence evidence-based planning down to the community level, were developed for each of the 16 districts by Local Councils using MICS6 data. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2019
